<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5954&amp;p=34742#p34742"><![CDATA[
I'm also having this issue occasionally.<br />Currently still on Windows 10 1703.<br /><br />The thing is I've noticed that frequently threads on the explorer.exe start to acumulate on waiting status until eventually the explorer process just locks up and crashes when enough &quot;stuck&quot; threads have accumulated.<br /><br /><br />Now, the thread that is common to all these ones that are stuck in waiting mode, is a thread belonging to ClassicStartMenu with a &quot;Start address&quot; reported sometimes as &quot;ClassicStartMenuDLL.dll!DllExecuteNamedCommand&quot;, other times reported as &quot;ClassicStartMenuDLL.dll!WaitDllInitThread&quot;, by Sysinternals Process Explorer.<br /><br />I hope this helps in any way.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=27181">JohnnyMartins</a> — Mon Nov 20, 2017 9:49 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
